like  I  do,  you  come  to  Texarkana  to  either  have  a  baby  or  see  a
movie, and we’ve done both. We’ve done the latter more than we’ve
done  the  former.  My  son  Alex  was  born  here  May  14,  1992.  Y’all
can do the math on that and quickly figure out that this Thursday
is not a day I will be looking forward to; he will be 16.

Also,  I  have  a  close  tie  here  in  that  my  Chief  of  Staff  in  my
Washington  office  grew  up  here,  was  educated  here  in  the  Tex-
arkana/Arkansas  Public  School  system  and  is  a  Texarkana  native.
