Chairman GORDON. Thank you, Mr. Hall. One of the things that
we learned from the report, Rising Above the Gathering Storm, was
really  disturbing,  and  that  is  that  approximately  63  percent  of  the
math teachers in our middle schools have neither a certification to
teach  math  or  a  major  in  math.  Ninety-three  percent  of  the  phys-

